tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows markedly elevated serum creatinine, indicating significant renal impairment, with associated proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria on urinalysis. Mildly elevated ALT and low alkaline phosphatase are noted. Urine is cloudy, brown, and has low specific gravity. No evidence of urinary infection. Findings suggest acute or chronic kidney dysfunction, possible nephrotic syndrome, and poor glycemic control. Clinical correlation and further nephrological and diabetic evaluation are recommended.
